instead of midterms, i do a "quizz-am" every other week. it helps students stay up with the material. the last week of class is ridiculous for students here, so i try to provide lots of mini-due dates (outlines, figures) ramping up to that week if they have final project.

it's my fav week teaching hematology! i get to amplify the historical work of mds who developed therapies to treat & eventually cure all. i especially love to highlight dr. don pinkel, who lives in slo & lectured at cp until his health declined.

100(!!)face masks were just dropped off by https://www.facemasksforsloco.org/ for sep participants. gratitude for helping the often overlooked members of our community stay safer! we require masks on site to get supplies or naloxone, this make it much easier!
